segment.source: Field Medic is an app that you can use to gather Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) log files for selected information categories.
segment.target: Field Medic is an app that you can use to gather Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) log files for selected information categories.

segment.source: You can also use Field Medic to gather general information about the phone.
segment.target: You can also use Field Medic to gather general information about the phone.

segment.source: Field Medic saves the ETW log files and the general information in a folder that is accessible using the USB Media Transfer Protocol (MTP).
segment.target: Field Medic saves the ETW log files and the general information in a folder that is accessible using the USB Media Transfer Protocol (MTP).

segment.source: Note MTP is enabled on all retail devices by default.
segment.target: Note MTP is enabled on all retail devices by default.

segment.source: It allows for the easy extraction of output files such as Field Medic reports without requiring TShell or other test tools to be enabled.
segment.target: It allows for the easy extraction of output files such as Field Medic reports without requiring TShell or other test tools to be enabled.

segment.source: However, you must disable kernel debugging interfaces over USB (KDNET, KDUSB) for MTP to work correctly.
segment.target: However, you must disable kernel debugging interfaces over USB (KDNET, KDUSB) for MTP to work correctly.

segment.source: There are two ways to install the Field Medic app.
segment.target: There are two ways to install the Field Medic app.

segment.source: Download it from the Store using the following link from your device: Field Medic app download.
segment.target: Download it from the Store using the following link from your device: Field Medic app download.

segment.source: The app is included with the MobileOS packages (in the FieldMedic folder) with a license and provisioning XML for partners who want to preload the app.
segment.target: The app is included with the MobileOS packages (in the FieldMedic folder) with a license and provisioning XML for partners who want to preload the app.
